{"title": "Pit Trap", "content": "\"You fell into a pitfall! This was your first pitfall in the Schwarzwelt, wasn't it? How did it feel as you fell? Anyway You've been introduced to the typical cheap trap. Be very careful from this point on.\"\n\nA hole in the ground that's somehow covered up so as to blend in with the surrounding terrain. Sometimes it's hidden beneath a Trap Door. Related to but not to be confused with Bottomless Pit. If it's not hidden, it's not a pit trap.\n\nA standard subversion is where character A sets up a pitfall for character B, B walks straight over the covered pit and doesn't fall in, and then character A tries to cross (possibly preceded by tentative testing first) and does fall in, Wile E. Coyote-style.\n\nPlatform Hell titles will have these, usually with no indication at all that it's a trap.\n\nOftentimes it is a Conspicuously Light Patch. If there's an angry creature waiting at the bottom, you may have run into an Antlion Monster.\n\nMay have something nasty at the bottom to do additional damage on impact, such as Spikes of Doom (possibly poisoned).", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PitTrap", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/ShinMegamiTenseiStrangeJourney", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/GingaNagareboshiGin", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Pokemon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VisualNovel/HigurashiWhenTheyCry", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/RanmaOneHalf", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MahouSenseiNegima", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/ExcelSaga", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Touhou", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/InabaOfTheMoonAndInabaOfTheEarth", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/YuGiOhCapsuleMonsters", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Asterix", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/BarbieAsRapunzel", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/TheLionKingOneAndAHalf", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/TheRescuersDownUnder", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Chang", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ThreeAmigos", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SwissFami